title: For Sale:  1998 Chevy Metro
postcontent:
Make no mistake: this vehicle is heavily used.  I had a rebuilt engine/transmission installed at ~ 150K and now it's ~ 178K.  It's a 1998, 3 cylinder (yes really), manual transmission Chevy Metro.  IR has a CD player, two front seats, and not much else.  I've stripped out the seats, plastic molding, and carpeting from the rear to make it easier to load gear in and out. Believe it or not, this was my daily driver and hog hunting "truck" in texas before we moved to OH.  It handles off road trails surprisingly well if you do your part to drive it carefully.

It gets 40+ MPG all day long and is surprisingly fun to drive if you like go-karts.  I can't recommend driving faster than 90MPH, but it'll do 65-75 just fine.  

I don't expect much.  in fact, I'd walk away smiling for $400.  I'll also accept random trades.  Maybe 2 serviceable Mosins, or one Mosin and 2 spam cans... Whatever.  I truly loved owning and driving this car, but no longer have the space or need for it.  You might get a good deal selling it for parts as there aren't many around and there is a small cult following who keeps these things running; I just don't have the time.
